title: Records Request: Complaints filed to the Indiana State Board of Animal Health

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Indiana Access to Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

-A copy of all complaints filed to the Indiana State Board of Animal Health, between January 1st, 2025 and the date of response to this request. 

I'm a journalist with the nonprofit newsroom Sentient. Any responsive documents will be used in reporting in the public interest, relating to safety of the U.S. food system and the welfare of farm animals.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Grey Moran

title: Records Request: Complaints and Inspection Reports of Livestock Abuse or Neglect

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Tennessee Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

-All complaints concerning livestock cruelty, including abuse or neglect, filed to the Tennessee Department of Agriculture, between May 1st, 2025 and the date of response to this request. The emails relevant to this search may include animal.health@tn.gov and samantha.beaty@tn.gov. 
-All inspection reports in response to a complaint concerning livestock cruelty, including abuse or neglect, filed to the Tennessee Department of Agriculture, between May 1st, 2025 and the date of response to this request. 

I'm a journalist with the nonprofit newsroom Sentient. Any responsive documents will be used in reporting in the public interest, relating to safety of the U.S. food system and the welfare of farm animals.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with Grey Moran.
